Simple Android animation for button or other elements 

The animation loads on entering the screen

Steps to follow.

1) Implement the AnimationListener interface
2) Define animation in anim folder (I created left to right and right to left two animation files.)
3) Load the animation with following command  "Animation animation=AnimationUtils.loadAnimation(this,R.anim.left_to_right);"
4) Add the animation listeners "animation.setAnimationListener(this);"
5) Get the target id (in this case the buttons )Button b1=(Button) findViewById(R.id.Button01);
6) Apply the animation